<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870501-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Careercom Closes PurchaseOf a Jostens Inc. Subsidiary</HL><DD> 05/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CRCM JOSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> MIDDLETOWN, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Careercom Corp. said it completed the acquisition of Jostens Inc.'s educational systems subsidiary for $20 million and 1.7 million shares.    The Jostens unit consists of 35 proprietary schools that generated 1986 revenue of $56 million, Careercom said.    As a result of the transaction, Jostens becomes the largest holder of Careercom, an operator of vocational schools, with 20%. Jostens, a Minneapolis maker of class rings, yearbooks and recognition awards, also acquired rights to buy as many as 217,186 additional Careercom shares for $11.41 each under certain conditions.    Careercom shares rose 62.5 cents, to $11.75, in national over-the-counter trading yesterday. In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Jostens's shares rose 62.5 cents to $20.625. </TEXT></DOC>